{"ID":270305, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"305\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs304.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs306.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 305<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">derstand the three principal rounds of Jacob&rsquo;s ladder<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span>&mdash;the telestial, the terrestrial, and the celestial\n  glories or kingdoms,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> where Paul saw and heard things which were not lawful for him to utter.<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> I\n  could explain a hundred fold more<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> than I ever have of the glories of the kingdoms manifested to me\n  in the vision,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> were I permitted, and were the people prepared to receive them.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The Lord deals with this people as a tender parent<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> with a child, communicating light and\n  intelligence and the knowledge of his ways<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> as they can bear it.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> The inhabitants of the earth are\n  asleep;<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> they know not the day of their visitation.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> The Lord hath set the bow in the cloud<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> for a\n  sign that while it shall be seen, seed time and harvest, summer and winter shall not fail; but when\n  it shall disappear, woe to that generation, for behold the end cometh quickly.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Calling and Election to Be Made Sure<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Contend earnestly<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> for the like precious<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> faith<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> with the Apostle Peter, &ldquo;and add to your faith\n  virtue,&rdquo; knowledge, temperance, patience, godliness, brotherly kindness, charity; &ldquo;for if these things\n  be in you, and abound, they make you that ye shall neither be barren nor unfruitful in the knowledge\n  of our Lord Jesus Christ.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> Another point, after having all these qualifications, he lays this\n  injunction upon the people &ldquo;to make your calling and election sure.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> He is emphatic upon this\n  subject&mdash;after adding all this virtue, knowledge,<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> etc., &ldquo;Make your calling and election sure.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span>\n  What is the secret&mdash;the starting point? &ldquo;According as His divine power hath given unto us all things\n  that pertain unto life and godliness.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> How did he obtain all things? Through the knowledge of Him\n  who hath called him.<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> There could not anything be given, pertaining to life and godliness,<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> without\n  knowledge. Woe!  woe!  woe to Christendom!&mdash;especially the divines and priests if this be true.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Salvation is for a man to be saved from all his enemies;<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> for until a man can triumph over\n  death,<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> he is not saved. A knowledge of the priesthood<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> alone will do this.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Devil&rsquo;s Punishment<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The spirits in the eternal world are like the spirits in this world.<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> When those have come into\n  this world and received<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106056\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106056)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106056)\">Gen. 28:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109603\"><a href=\"ja